This paper presents a method for incorporating task reward into a maximum likelihood framework for structured output prediction, which is a problem commonly studied in machine learning and natural language processing. The paper specifically focuses on experiments with neural sequence to sequence models for speech recognition and machine translation, which are subfields of computer science related to natural language processing and computer vision. Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
